kshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bayworth, Abingdon, Berkshire, England":"Bayworth, Berkshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"5 Apr 1145–7 Jan 1217":"5 April 1145–7 January 1217","1145–1217":"1145–1217","1155–Female":"1155–Deceased","1145–1175":"1145–1175","1175–Female":"1175–Deceased","1181–Male":"1181–Deceased","1115–1175":"1115–1175","1123–Female":"1123–Deceased","5 Apr 1145":"5 April 1145","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","7 Jan 1217":"7 January 1217","1181":"1181","1217":"1217","1215":"1215","1115":"1115","ABT 1143":"about 1143","1123":"1123","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","ABT 1181":"about 1181","Bayworth, Berkshire, England":"Bayworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom","Buckland, Berkshire, England":"Buckland, Berkshire, England","Bayworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bayworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom","Bayworth, Abingdon, Berkshire, England":"Bayworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Sandford","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of numerous places in England with names derived from Old English <i>sand</i> ‘sand’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford, river crossing’, such as Sandford in Warcop (Westmorland), Sandford in Sonning and Dry Sandford in Abingdon (both Berkshire), Sandford on Thames and Sandford Saint Martin (both Oxfordshire), Great and Little Sampford (Essex), Sandford Orcas (Dorset), Sandford, Sampford Courtney, Sampford Peverell, and Sampford Spiney (all Devon), Sampford Arundel and Sampford Brett (both Somerset), and Sandford (Shropshire). See also   Sandiford  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Samford","meanings":["English (Essex): variant of   Sandford  ."]},{"name":"Sanderford","meanings":["English: variant of   Sandford  ."]},{"name":"Sanford","meanings":["English (Devon): variant of   Sandford  ."]},{"name":"Sandiford","meanings":["English (Lancashire): variant of   Sandifer  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":69,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Sandford II was born on 5 April 1145, in Bayworth, Berkshire, England, his father, Jordan de Sandford, was 30 and his mother, Mrs Jordan Sandford, was 22. He married Katherine Alice Basset in 1173, in Bayworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died on 7 January 1217, in Buckland, Berkshire, England, at the age of 71."},"et":{"5 Apr 1145–7 Jan 1217":"5. aprill 1145–7. jaanuar 1217","1145–1217":"1145–1217","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1145–1175":"1145–1175","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1181–Male":"1181–Surnud","1115–1175":"1115–1175","1123–Female":"1123–Surnud","5 Apr 1145":"5. aprill 1145","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","7 Jan 1217":"7. jaanuar 1217","1181":"1181","1217":"1217","1215":"1215","1115":"1115","ABT 1143":"umbes 1143","1123":"1123","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","ABT 1181":"umbes 1181","Bayworth, Berkshire, England":"Bayworth, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Buckland, Berkshire, England":"Buckland, Berkshire, England","Bayworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bayworth, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bayworth, Abingdon, Berkshire, England":"Bayworth, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"5 Apr 1145–7 Jan 1217":"5. huhtikuuta 1145–7. tammikuuta 1217","1145–1217":"1145–1217","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1145–1175":"1145–1175","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1181–Male":"1181–Kuollut","1115–1175":"1115–1175","1123–Female":"1123–Kuollut","5 Apr 1145":"5. huhtikuuta 1145","1175":"1175","1173":"1173","7 Jan 1217":"7. tammikuuta 1217","1181":"1181","1217":"1217","1215":"1215","1115":"1115","ABT 1143":"noin 1143","1123":"1123","1145":"1145","1155":"1155","ABT 1181":"noin 1181","Bayworth, Berkshire, England":"Bayworth, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Buckland, Berkshire, England":"Buckland, Berkshire, England","Bayworth, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bayworth, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Bayworth, Abingdon, Berkshire, England":"Bayworth, Berkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"5 Apr 1145–7 Jan 1217":"5 avril 1145–7 janvier 1217","1145–1217":"1145–1217","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1145–1175":"1